contents: Autism spectrum disorder (ASD) is a range of complex disorders with symptoms that _____(6)_____ significantly from individual to individual. ASD manifests in social impairments, communication difficulties, and restricted, repetitive behavior patterns.  The most severe form of ASD is known as autistic disorder, _____(7)_____ is sometimes simply referred to as “autism.” Asperger syndrome is a milder form of ASD. Other disorders vary in severity and symptoms. ASD occurs in all ethnic, socioeconomic, and ______(8)______ males are four times more likely to have ASD than females.
